    "summary": "Sales at U.S. retailers rose modestly in April, with spending proving more uneven in the face of higher fuel prices.  There is “little sign” that higher fuel costs are forcing consumers to cut back dramatically on their overall spending as of yet, he notes, though that pressure is expected to build in the coming months.  Nominal spending on essentials held up relatively well in April, though much of that is likely a result of higher prices.",
